properties.text: The Mini quickly became a design classic, and took to Britain's roads for the first time in 1959. It is one of the best-selling British cars in history.
Elvis "The King Of Rock" was crowned in the same decade as the Queen. Elvis had two of the best selling singles of the 50s, All Shook Up in 1957 and Jailhouse Rock in 1958.
20 million people in the UK watched the Queen's coronation in 1953. Cameras had never been allowed in Westminster Abbey before, and the event caused a boom in sales of the new technology.

Post-war Britain started the 1950s hard-up and hurting. Food rations were in place until 1954, there were unexploded bombs in the streets, and Britain's international standing was shaken by the Suez crisis.
